g2:c.TYPE-IN-BOX.g2:a.VALUE-ON-ACTIVATION: Hello, this is G2 talking over a socket

g2:c.BORDERLESS-FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT:
To utilize this demonstration, proceed with the following: 1. Make sure the Socket Manager bridge is running (the g2-java-example-interface will be GREEN when connected to the bridge). 2. Create a Server socket by selecting create-socket from SERVER-SOCKET-1. 3. Create a Client socket by selecting create-socket from CLIENT-SOCKET-1. 4. Send some text over the Client socket to the Server socket by selecting send-data-over-socket from CLIENT-SOCKET-1.
Additionally, you can specify a file for TEST-FILE and by selecting the 'Select to send above file over socket' button, the contents of the file will be sent to the Server socket.
NOTE: Be sure to include a carriage return after the last line in your test file. Failure to do so will exclude the last line from being sent.
To terminate the socket connection select reset-socket-i/o from both CLIENT-SOCKET-1 and SERVER-SOCKET-1.
